(128, 'What is GEM Portal?', 'The Government e-Marketplace (GEM) is an online platform for public procurement by government organizations..', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:26:16'),
(129, 'Why GEM Registration is Important?', 'It allows businesses to access government tenders, ensuring transparency and providing growth opportunities.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(130, 'What are the Documents Required for GEM Registration?', 'PAN, GST, Udyam (if applicable), bank account details, business registration certificate, etc.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(131, 'What is the Registration Fee for GEM Portal?', 'The registration fee depends on the turnover and product category.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(132, 'What is the Importance of the Make in India Certificate?', 'It helps businesses qualify for government projects focused on promoting indigenous products.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(133, 'How Can I Get Vendor Assessment Done?', 'Vendor assessment is done after paying the caution money and fulfilling the OEM requirements.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(134, 'Is GEM Registration Free?', 'No, there may be nominal fees involved depending on the business size and product category.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(135, 'Can International Vendors Register on GEM?', 'Yes, provided they meet the criteria set by the Indian government for international businesses.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(136, 'How Long Does the GEM Registration Process Take?', 'It can take anywhere from a few days to a couple of weeks, depending on the completeness of your application.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(137, 'Can I Modify My GEM Profile After Registration?', 'Yes, registered vendors can update their profile anytime on the GEM portal.', 'GEM Registration', 'gem-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:25:21', '2026-01-20 12:25:21'),
(138, 'What is the Tamil Nadu Shops and Establishments Act?', 'The Tamil Nadu Shops and Establishments Act is a state law that regulates the working conditions, rights of employees, hours of work, holidays, payment of wages, and other conditions in shops, commercial establishments, and related workplaces within Tamil Nadu..', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:39:45'),
(139, 'What is the validity of a shop act license?', 'The validity of a Shop Act license differs by state but is typically issued for 1 to 5 years. After this period, it must be renewed to remain valid.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(140, 'Which entities are required to obtain the shop act license?', 'All shops, commercial establishments, offices, hotels, restaurants, theaters, and other places of public amusement or entertainment must obtain the Shop Act license, except certain exempted government and local authority offices.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(141, 'Is the shop act registration applicable for the establishments of the central and state government?', 'No, establishments of the central and state government are generally exempt from Shop Act registration. The Act mainly applies to private commercial establishments.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(142, 'Are the shop act registrations valid in all states/UTs across India?', 'No, Shop Act registration is regulated by individual states/UTs, and registration obtained in one state is not automatically valid in another. Each state/UT has its own rules, and separate registration is needed if operating in multiple states.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(143, 'Does a factory owner need to register under the Shops and Establishments Registration Act?', 'No, factory owners do not need to register under the Shops and Establishments Act if the premises are covered under the Factories Act, 1948. The Shop Act applies to commercial establishments that are not classified as factories.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(144, 'What details are to be filled in the Shop Act Registration form?', 'The form typically requires the establishment’s name and address, details of the employer and employees, nature of business, PAN, proof of address, number of employees, date of commencement, and other relevant documents.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(145, 'Is it necessary for the establishment to get self-registered under the Shops and Establishments Registration Act?', 'Yes, most states/UTs require all eligible establishments to self-register under the Shops and Establishments Act within a specific timeframe after commencing business.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(146, 'What is the fundamental objective of the Shops and Establishments Act?', 'The primary objective is to provide better working conditions for employees, regulate work hours and holidays, protect workers’ rights, ensure payment of wages, and promote the well-being of staff in commercial establishments.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(147, 'Is it necessary to take approval from the labor department?', 'Yes, approval or registration from the local Labor Department is generally mandatory for most establishments under the Shops and Establishments Act. This ensures compliance with labor laws and proper record-keeping.', 'Shop & Establishment', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', 1, '2026-01-20 12:38:43', '2026-01-20 12:38:43'),
(148, 'What is ISO certification?', 'ISO certification is an official recognition awarded to businesses or organizations that meet international standards set by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO). It demonstrates a commitment to quality, safety, efficiency, or other specific benchmarks.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(149, 'What is the validity period of ISO certification?', 'ISO certificates are typically valid for three years, subject to annual surveillance audits. After three years, the certificate must be renewed through a re-certification process..', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:45:58'),
(150, 'Is ISO certification available in my area?', 'Yes, ISO certification can be obtained globally. Accredited certification bodies operate in most regions and can arrange assessments and audits regardless of your location.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(151, 'How does international standardization benefit businesses?', 'International standardization boosts business credibility, improves process efficiency, opens access to global markets, ensures product consistency and safety, and enhances customer confidence.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(152, 'What distinguishes ISO certification from accreditation?', 'ISO certification is given to organizations for meeting specific ISO standards. Accreditation, on the other hand, is the formal recognition of a certification body’s competence to issue ISO certificates.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(153, 'Is renewal necessary for my ISO certificate?', 'Yes, you must renew your ISO certification every three years. Annual surveillance audits are needed to maintain its validity throughout the certificate period.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(154, 'How do the various accreditation bodies for ISO certification differ?', 'Accreditation bodies are organizations that evaluate and approve certification agencies. Different bodies may be recognized in different countries or industries, but all ensure impartiality and that proper standards are upheld.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(155, 'Who is responsible for issuing ISO certification?', 'ISO certificates are issued by accredited certification bodies (also called registrars), not by ISO itself. These bodies independently verify that organizations meet the required standards.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(156, 'What does our ISO Registration Package include?', 'An ISO registration package usually covers consultation, documentation, implementation support, internal audits, the official certification audit, and ongoing assistance for maintaining and renewing the certificate.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(157, 'Will I receive a certificate during the pre-audit phase?', 'No, official ISO certificates are only awarded after a successful certification audit. The pre-audit phase is for preparation and internal assessment.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(158, 'Can I select any ISO accreditation?', 'You should select an accreditation body that is recognized and respected in your industry and by your clients. Choosing a reputable and internationally recognized body ensures wider acceptance of your ISO certificate.', 'ISO Certification', 'iso-certification', 1, '2026-01-20 12:43:45', '2026-01-20 12:43:45'),
(159, 'What is FoSCos?', 'FoSCos (Food Safety Compliance System) is the official online portal launched by FSSAI for food business registration, licensing, renewals, and compliance across India. Through FoSCos, food business operators (FBOs) can manage their FSSAI license and ensure compliance with food safety regulations.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(160, 'Is GST registration necessary for FSSAI?', 'GST registration is not mandatory for obtaining an FSSAI license; however, GST details are often required for food businesses with taxable turnover. Linking GST with FSSAI registration can streamline business operations and compliance.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(161, 'How can I obtain an FSSAI certificate?', 'To obtain an FSSAI certificate, apply through the FoSCos portal (fssai.gov.in/foscos) by filling out the required application, uploading documents, and paying the applicable fee. Once approved, you’ll receive your FSSAI registration or license certificate online.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(162, 'Who qualifies for exemption from the FoSCos license?', 'Certain small-scale food businesses, such as petty retailers, hawkers, and businesses with annual turnover below the prescribed limit, may qualify for exemption from an FSSAI license but may still require FSSAI registration.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(163, 'How can I download the FSSAI registration certificate from the FoSCos portal?', 'Log in to your FoSCos account, go to the application dashboard, find your approved FSSAI registration or license, and click on the “Download certificate” option to get your certificate in PDF format.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(164, 'What is the procedure for renewing my registration or license after it expires?', 'To renew an expired FSSAI license or registration, log in to the FoSCos portal, select “Renewal,” fill in the renewal form, upload required documents, and pay the renewal fee before the license’s expiry date to avoid penalties.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(165, 'What steps are involved in obtaining the FoSCos license?', 'Steps include: Create an account on the FoSCos portal, select the license/registration type, complete the online application, upload supporting documents, make payment, and track the application status until approval.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(166, 'How can I acquire a food license in Chennai?', 'Food businesses in Chennai must register and apply for an FSSAI license via the FoSCos portal, submitting correct documents and fees specific to Tamil Nadu regulations.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(167, 'How do I apply for FSSAI registration in Tamil Nadu?', 'Visit the FoSCos portal, select Tamil Nadu as your state, fill the FSSAI application form, upload the necessary documents, and submit the application for official review and approval.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(168, 'What does the vegetarian symbol on FSSAI products signify?', 'The green vegetarian symbol on FSSAI labels shows that the food product is entirely vegetarian, containing no animal-derived ingredients, for easy identification by consumers.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(169, 'What does the fortified FSSAI logo represent?', 'The fortified FSSAI logo indicates that the food product contains added essential nutrients (fortification) above standard requirements, promoting better nutrition.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(170, 'What is FSSAI\'s tagline?', 'FSSAI’s official tagline is “Ensuring Safe & Nutritious Food” for all consumers in India.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(171, 'How can I renew my FSSAI registration?', 'You can renew your FSSAI registration online through the FoSCos portal by logging in, selecting the renewal option, filling out the required details, and submitting specified documents and renewal fees.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(172, 'Is it possible to operate a food business without FSSAI registration?', 'No, operating a food business without valid FSSAI registration or license is illegal in India. All food businesses, regardless of size, must register or obtain an FSSAI license as per FSSAI regulations.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(173, 'Which types of products require an FSSAI license?', 'All food products meant for human consumption—including packaged foods, beverages, dairy, meat, bakery goods, and food additives—require an FSSAI license before production or sale.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(174, 'Can an expired FSSAI license be renewed?', 'Yes, an expired FSSAI license can be renewed within 30 days of expiry via the FoSCos portal. Delays beyond this period may require a fresh FSSAI application and may attract penalties.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(175, 'How can I obtain a food license for a fruit business?', 'Fruit business owners must apply for an FSSAI registration or license on the FoSCos portal, providing business details, documents, and paying the prescribed fee, specific to the category of fruit handling or sales.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(176, 'How can I check the status of my FSSAI application online?', 'Check your FSSAI application status by logging into FoSCos, navigating to the “Track Application Status” section, and entering your application or reference number.', 'FSSAI Food License', 'fssai-food-license', 1, '2026-01-20 12:59:12', '2026-01-20 12:59:12'),
(177, 'How to Download Your IEC Certificate?', 'Log in to the DGFT (Directorate General of Foreign Trade) portal with your credentials, go to the “IEC Profile Management” section, and select “Print IEC Certificate” to download your IEC certificate in PDF format..', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:42'),
(178, 'How to Modify Your IEC Code?', 'To modify your IEC code details (such as address or entity name), log in to the DGFT portal, navigate to “Modify IEC,” update the required information, upload supporting documents, and submit for approval.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(179, 'How to Edit and Renew Your IEC?', 'IEC renewal and editing is done via the DGFT portal. Select “Update IEC,” make the necessary changes, upload documents, and submit. Renewal must be done every year to keep your IEC active as per DGFT guidelines.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(180, 'Which DSC (Digital Signature Certificate) is Required for IEC Code?', 'A valid Class 2 or Class 3 Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) registered in the name of the authorized signatory is required for filing and modifying IEC applications on the DGFT portal.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(181, 'How Can I Print My IEC Certificate?', 'After issuance, log in to the DGFT portal, go to the IEC section, and use the “Print IEC Certificate” option to print your IEC in a downloadable format.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(182, 'What Are the Technical Requirements for Filing an IEC Number?', 'You need a stable internet connection, compatible browser (latest Chrome, Firefox, or Edge), scanned supporting documents, and an active DSC (Digital Signature Certificate) for secure submission on the DGFT portal.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(183, 'Is IEC Number Required for Service Exporters?', 'Yes, service exporters from India generally need an IEC number to receive payments in foreign currency or for conducting cross-border service transactions as per RBI and DGFT rules.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(184, 'Who Issues the IEC?', 'The IEC (Import Export Code) is issued online by the Directorate General of Foreign Trade (DGFT), Ministry of Commerce and Industry, Government of India.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(185, 'Which Browsers Are Compatible with the DGFT Portal?', 'The DGFT portal works best with updated versions of Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, and Microsoft Edge. Avoid using outdated or unsupported browsers for error-free application.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(186, 'What Is the Validity of the IEC Number?', 'The IEC number is valid for the lifetime of the business, but you must update/confirm your IEC registration annually on the DGFT portal to keep it active as per new regulations.', 'Import Export Code', 'import-export-code', 1, '2026-01-20 13:02:03', '2026-01-20 13:02:03'),
(187, 'How can I obtain a Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) online?', 'Obtaining your Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) online is simple, fast, and affordable with Ensurekar. We provide a seamless end-to-end process to help individuals and organizations get their DSCs quickly and securely. \n\nWith Ensurekar, you get:\n• Competitive pricing with transparent costs and no hidden fees\n• Expert support throughout your DSC application and issuance process\n• Fully digital, paperless procedure for maximum convenience\n• Compatibility for all government, corporate, and legal document signing needs\n• Fast verification and issuance, delivered securely to your doorstep\n• Trusted by thousands of customers for reliable digital certification\n\nChoose Ensurekar for your DSC online and experience hassle-free, affordable, and compliant digital signature solutions tailored to your needs. Start your application today and secure your documents the smart way!', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:16:57'),
(188, 'How does a Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) work for signing documents online?', 'A DSC authenticates your identity electronically and allows you to sign documents digitally. The digital signature is encrypted and legally valid, ensuring the integrity of online contracts, tax filings, and compliance documents.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(189, 'Who is authorized to issue a digital signature certificate online?', 'Licensed Certifying Authorities (CAs) approved by the Controller of Certifying Authorities (CCA), Government of India, are authorized to issue DSCs. Examples include eMudhra, Sify, NSDL, and others.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(190, 'Can I get a DSC registration for free?', 'No, obtaining a legally valid DSC requires a fee. Certifying Authorities charge for issuing Digital Signature Certificates to cover verification and hardware token costs.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(191, 'What is the cost of obtaining a digital signature certificate online?', 'The DSC cost varies by provider, type, and validity period. Typically, prices start from ₹2,000 plus GST for signature or encryption DSC, and about ₹2,750 plus GST for a combo. Additional token and delivery charges may apply.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(192, 'Is there a limit to how many DSC registrations one can hold?', 'There’s no strict limit for individuals or organizations; you can have multiple DSCs for different purposes or entities, provided each is acquired lawfully.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(193, 'What is the difference between a digital certificate and a digital signature?', 'A digital certificate is an electronic ID (issued by a CA) that proves your identity online. A digital signature is the encrypted output generated by using the certificate to sign a document electronically.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(194, 'How long is a Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) valid for online signing?', 'DSCs are usually valid for 1 or 2 years. After expiration, they must be renewed for continued online use.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(195, 'Why is DSC registration necessary?', 'DSC registration ensures legally recognized e-signatures, protects data integrity, enables secure online transactions, and is often mandatory for e-filing with government, GST, MCA, and income tax portals.', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
(196, 'Who issues the Digital Signature Certificate online?', 'DSCs are issued online by authorized Certifying Authorities (CAs) licensed by India\'s Controller of Certifying Authorities (CCA).', 'Digital Signature Certificate', 'digital-signature-certificate', 1, '2026-01-20 13:15:45', '2026-01-20 13:15:45'),
